<p />
<h3><a name="Associate_Professor_University_o"></a> Associate Professor, University of Illinois at Chicago, 01/2009 - present </h3>
<p /> <ul>
<li> ECE 531: Detection and Estimation Theory; Spring 2009, Spring 2010,  <a href="http://www.ece.uic.edu/~devroye/courses/ECE531/" target="_top">Spring 2011,</a> <br /> <a href="http://www.ece.uic.edu/~devroye/courses/ECE531/ECE531-devroye-S09.pdf" target="_top">Spring 2009 teaching evaluations,</a> <a href="http://www.ece.uic.edu/~devroye/courses/ECE531/ECE531-devroye-S10.pdf" target="_top">Spring 2010 teaching evaluations</a>,  <a href="http://www.ece.uic.edu/~devroye/courses/ECE531/ECE531-Devroye-S11.pdf" target="_top">Spring 2011 teaching evaluations</a>
</li> <li> ECE 534: Elements of Information Theory, Fall 2009, Fall 2010, Fall 2011, Fall 2013, Fall 2017, <a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/bin/view/ECE534" target="_top">Fall 2018</a><br> <a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/pub/Devroye/WebHome/Fall_2017-Elements_of_Info_Theory.pdf" target="_top">Fall 2017 ECE 534 teaching evaluations,</a> <a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/pub/Devroye/WebHome/FALL_2013-Elements_of_Info_Theory.pdf" target="_top">Fall 2013 ECE 534 teaching evaluations,</a><a href="http://www.ece.uic.edu/~devroye/courses/ECE534/ECE534-Fall2011-Devroye.pdf" target="_top">Fall 2011 ECE 534 teaching evaluations</a>,  <a href="http://www.ece.uic.edu/~devroye/courses/ECE534/ECE534-Fall2010-Devroye.pdf" target="_top">Fall 2010 ECE 534 teaching evaluations</a>, <a href="http://www.ece.uic.edu/~devroye/courses/ECE534/ECE534_Fall_2009_overallscores+comments.pdf" target="_top"> Fall 2009 ECE 534 teaching evaluations</a>
</li> <li> ECE 341: Probability and Random Processes for Engineers, Spring 2012, Spring 2013, Spring 2015, Fall 2016 <br><a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/pub/Devroye/WebHome/ECE341-Fall2016.pdf" target="_top">Fall 2016 ECE 341 teaching evaluations,</a><a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/pub/Devroye/WebHome/ECE341-Spring2015.pdf" target="_top">Spring 2015 ECE 341 teaching evaluations,</a><a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/pub/Devroye/WebHome/ECE341_Spring_2013_overallscorescomments.pdf" target="_top"> Spring 2013 ECE 341 teaching evaluations,</a><a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/pub/Devroye/WebHome/ECE341_Spring_2012_overallscorescomments.pdf" target="_top"> Spring 2012 ECE 341 teaching evaluations</a>
</li></ul> 
<p />
To be taken with a grain of salt, <a href="http://www.ratemyprofessors.com/ShowRatings.jsp?tid=1344229" target="_top">my ratemyprofessor page</a>
<p />
 <img alt="" src="https://www.cs.uic.edu/pub/Devroye/WebHome/tash-hat.jpg" width="200" class="inlinePictureRight"/>
<h3><a name="Past_Experience"></a> Past Experience </h3>
<strong>Lecturer, Harvard University, 07/2007-07/2008</strong>
<p /> <ul>
<li> AM21a: Mathematical Methods in the Sciences, Fall 2007. 
</li> <li> AM21b: Mathematical Methods in the Sciences, Spring 2008.
</li></ul> 
<p />
<strong>Teaching Assistant, Harvard University, 09/2004-05/2006</strong>
<p /> <ul>
<li> ES102: Introduction to Operations Research, Spring 2006. Students rated overall 4.8/5.0. 
</li> <li> AM106:  Applied Algebra and Combinatorics, Fall 2005. Nominated for best TF award. Students rated overall 4.8/5.0.
</li> <li> ES156: Signals and Systems, Spring 2005.  Recipient of Certificate of Distinction in Teaching. Students rated overall 4.86/5.0.
</li> <li> AM106: Applied Abstract Algebra and Combinatorics, Fall 2004.
</li></ul>  </div><!-- /patternTopic-->
